Subject: DES3, input new data after each DES
Message-ID: <67DA9CD9@kiss.wlink.nl>
Date: 15 Jun 94 20:29:01 GMT
Organization: KISS Software Support, Almelo, The Netherlands
Lines: 28

The DES3 below uses blockexpantion, swapping the upper 4 bits (h_n) from bytes
in the first half-block with the lower 4 bits (l_n) from bytes in the second
half-block.

In case of blockexpantion on a 4-byte block (BE4): 

Before:                     After:

   h_0 h_1  h_2 h_3            l_2 l_3  h_2 h_3

   l_0 l_1  l_2 l_3            l_0 l_1  h_0 h_1

DES3:

   DES(K1)|BE16|DES(K2)|BE32|CBC(K3)

K1,K2,K3 are noncoherent DES keys.

I'd appreciate it if someone could comment on this comparing it to:

   DES(K1)|DES(K2)|CBC(K3)

Keeping in mind that I'd like to question the multiplying property of DES,
especially in case of, lets say, a DES1000 (with an 8-byte block?).

Thanks in advance,
Andy

